  "doc_id": "39029",
  "text": "Note that the PNS workers received much less than the 5 rem per year currently permitted by the Nuclear Regulatory Commission-actually receiving only about 0.5 rem per year [CITATION_1] . Yet this was enough to greatly increase their risk of lung cancer. Whereas most of the excess PNS lung cancer deaths are probably from this susceptible subgroup, in the high-dose studies this group would become relatively unimportant in the total deaths. However, in setting standards to protect nuclear workers, it is this subgroup which has to be protected.",
